.TH "__ssp_set_stop_bits" 9 "__ssp_set_stop_bits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__ssp_set_stop_bits \- set the number of stop bits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __ssp_set_stop_bits
.BI "(struct sifive_serial_port *ssp "  ","
.BI "char nstop "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssp" 12
pointer to a struct sifive_serial_port
.IP "nstop" 12
1 or 2 (stop bits)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Program the SiFive UART referred to by \fIssp\fP to use \fInstop\fP stop bits.
